{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb9711220-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3","identifier":"/us/usc/t39/s3663"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3663"},"text":"§ 3663.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Appellate review","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A person, including the Postal Service, adversely affected or aggrieved by a final order or decision of the Postal Regulatory Commission may, within 30 days after such order or decision becomes final, institute proceedings for review thereof by filing a petition in the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia. The court shall review the order or decision in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s706"},"text":"section 706 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", and chapter 158 and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2112"},"text":"section 2112 of title 28","children":[],"tail":", on the basis of the record before the Commission."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb9711221-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/435/tII/s205"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–435, title II, § 205","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/3217"},"text":"120 Stat. 3217","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb9711222-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb9711223-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"prio